result.execSummary:
The defendant Erin L Zurcher was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Erin L Zurcher in court with attorney John H. Wallace. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court apologizes to parties, matter was set this morning, did offer the parties to reschedule but due to distance, Defendant wished to continue to today.

Court questions Defendant.

There is an agreement.

Defendant will plead to single count as charged in information.

Parties are willing to proceed without a PSI being ordered.

Atty Knaapen states the agreement.
Atty Wallace concurs.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.

Defendant enters a plea of: NO CONTEST.

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney Wallace for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge.

Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge.
Court finds the defendant guilty.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Court has a number of factors to consider to determine sentencing.

BY THE COURT:
